#Text=[0520] Preparation A1, Step 2: A sample of (1R,6S)-6-benzyloxycarbonylamin-o-cyclohex-3-enecarboxylic acid methyl ester (91.4 g) was dissolved in MeOH (500 mL) prior to the dropwise addition of NaOH (25.3 g) in water (95 mL).
#Text=After 3 h, the solution was partially concentrated and an Et.sub.2O/water mixture was added.
#Text=The aqueous layer was separated and was acidified (pH.about.2) with concentrated HCl.
#Text=The resulting mixture was extracted with EtOAc.
#Text=The combined organic layers were washed with water and brine before they were dried, filtered, and concentrated to give (1R,6S)-6-benzyloxycarbonylamino-cyclohex-3-enecarboxylic acid (72.7 g).
#Text=MS found: (M+H).sup.+=276.2.

#Text=[0521] Preparation A1, Step 3: A sample of (1R,6S)-6-benzyloxycarbonylamin-o-cyclohex-3-enecarboxylic acid (72 g) was dissolved in CH.sub.2Cl.sub.2 (750 mL) prior to the addition of CDI (50.9 g).
#Text=After 2.5 h water was added, and the solution was extracted with CH.sub.2Cl.sub.2.
#Text=The combined organic layers were dried, filtered, and concentrated.
#Text=The resulting material was dissolved in CH.sub.2Cl.sub.2 and ammonia gas was bubbled through the solution for 1.5 h.
#Text=After stirring overnight, the majority of the solvent was removed and Et.sub.2O was added.
#Text=The product precipitated as a white solid and was collected to give (1R,6S)-6-carbamoyl-cyclohex-3--enyl)-carbamic acid benzyl ester (61.5 g).
#Text=MS found: (M+H).sup.+=275.3.
#Text=[0522] Preparation A1, Step 4: A sample of (1R,6S)-6-carbamoyl-cyclohex-3--enyl)-carbamic acid benzyl ester (30.7 g) was dissolved in THF (1100 mL) and NMP (220 mL).
#Text=At -78.degree.
#Text=C., 2.3M n-BuLi (96.3 mL) was added dropwise.
#Text=After 2 h, a solution of Boc.sub.2O (24.4 g) in THF (40 mL) was added dropwise.
#Text=This solution was stirred 1.2 h before it was quenched with a saturated NH.sub.4Cl solution.
#Text=Water and Et.sub.2O were added.
#Text=The organic layer was filtered then washed with water, brine, dried, filtered, and concentrated.
#Text=Flash chromatography of the resulting residue gave (1R,6S)-(6-tert-butoxycarbonylaminocarbonyl-cyclohex-3-enyl)-carbami-c acid benzyl ester (29.2 g).
#Text=MS found: (M+Na).sup.+=397.4.
#Text=[0523] Preparation A1, Step 5: A sample of (1R,6S)-(6-tert-butoxycarbonyl--aminocarbonyl-cyclohex-3-enyl)-carbamic acid benzyl ester (29.0 g) was dissolved in THF (1290 mL).
#Text=This was cooled in an ice/brine bath prior to the addition of n-BuLi (1.5 mL, 2.4M).
#Text=After 30 min, iodine (59.0 g) was added in a single portion.
#Text=The bath was removed, and the reaction was warmed to rt overnight.
#Text=The resulting solution was quenched with saturated thiosulfate solution.
#Text=Water and EtOAc were added.
#Text=The organic layer was washed with water, brine, dried, filtered, and concentrated.

#Text=The resulting slurry was diluted with Et.sub.2O and (1R,2S,4S,5R)-2-benzyloxycarbonylamino-4-iodo-7-oxo-6-aza-bicyclo[3.2.1]o-ctane-6-carboxylic acid tert-butyl ester (22.8 g) was collected by vacuum filtration.
#Text=MS found: (M-C.sub.5H.sub.8O.sub.2+H).sup.+=401.1.

#Text=[0524] Preparation A1, Step 6: A sample of (1R,2S,4S,5R)-2-benzyloxycarbon-ylamino-4-iodo-7-oxo-6-aza-bicyclo[3.2.1]octane-6-carboxylic acid tert-butyl ester (43.3 g) was dissolved in benzene (580 mL) prior to the addition of Bu.sub.3SnH (27.8 g) and AIBN (0.7 g).
#Text=The resulting mixture was warmed to a gentle reflux for 3 h.
#Text=After cooling, the solvent was removed and hexane was added.

#Text=The resulting white solid was collected by vacuum filtration to give the title compound, (1R,2S,5R)-2-Benzyloxycarbo-nylamino-7-oxo-6-aza-bicyclo[3.2.1]octane-6-carboxylic acid tert-butyl ester (29.5 g).
#Text=MS found: (M+Na).sup.+=397.4.
